.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="218" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1155,1368,1498]" box="[160,285,1368,1394]" pageId="28" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,285,1368,1394]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="218">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1155,1368,1498]" pageId="28" pageNumber="218">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Costa &amp; Duarte &amp; Iannuzzi &amp; Grossi" authorityYear="2022" box="[160,253,1404,1429]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Tetragus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[160,253,1404,1429]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="218">Tetragus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an anagram originating from the word ‘Strategus’, formed by the exclusion of the first ‘s’ plus an exchange of position between the syllable ‘ra’ and the vowel ‘e’. The name is masculine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="218" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1156,1557,1722]" box="[160,262,1557,1583]" pageId="28" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="218">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1156,1557,1722]" pageId="28" pageNumber="218">
<taxonomicName authority="Costa &amp; Duarte &amp; Iannuzzi &amp; Grossi, 2022" authorityName="Costa &amp; Duarte &amp; Iannuzzi &amp; Grossi" authorityYear="2022" box="[160,253,1593,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Tetragus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[160,253,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="218">Tetragus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[263,370,1593,1618]" pageId="28" pageNumber="218" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[501,603,1593,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Strategus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[501,603,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="218">Strategus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the tuberculate head and pronotum with an anterior horn but is separated by the bidentate mandibles; metatibia truncated at apex; tergite VII without stridulatory apparatus; female pronotum bearing a strong and transverse anterior tubercle, combined with a deep concavity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
